Uses of Package
javaslang.collection

  • Packages that use javaslang.collection 
    Package Description
    javaslang.collection
    Immutable collections based on Traversable like the linked list List and the lazy linked list Stream.
    javaslang.control
    Control structures like Match, the disjoint union type Either, the optional value type Option and Try for exception handling.
    javaslang.test
    A property check framework built around Property which integrates well with unit test frameworks like junit.
  • Classes in javaslang.collection used by javaslang.collection 
    Class and Description
    BinaryTree
    A binary tree implementation where each node keeps a value.
    BinaryTree.AbstractBinaryTree
    An abstract binary tree implementation which just overrides equals, hashCode and toString.
    BinaryTree.Branch
    Representation of a binary tree branch.
    BinaryTree.Leaf
    Representation of a binary tree leaf.
    BinaryTree.Nil
    The singleton instance of the empty binary tree.
    List
    A List is an eager sequence of elements.
    List.AbstractList
    This class is needed because the interface List cannot use default methods to override Object's non-final methods equals, hashCode and toString.
    List.Nil
    Representation of the singleton empty List.
    Queue
    A Queue stores elements allowing a first-in-first-out (FIFO) retrieval.
    RoseTree
    A rose tree implementation, i.e.
    RoseTree.AbstractRoseTree
    An abstract rose tree implementation which just overrides equals, hashCode and toString.
    RoseTree.Branch
    Representation of a rose tree branch.
    RoseTree.Leaf
    Representation of a rose tree leaf.
    RoseTree.Nil
    The singleton instance of the empty rose tree.
    RoseTree.NonNil
    Implementors of this tagging interface indicate that they are not Nil.
    Seq
    Interface for sequential, traversable data structures.
    Stack
    A Stack stores elements allowing a last-in-first-out (LIFO) retrieval.
    Stream
    A Stream is lazy sequence of elements which may be infinitely long.
    Stream.AbstractStream
    This class is needed because the interface Stream cannot use default methods to override Object's non-final methods equals, hashCode and toString.
    Stream.Nil
    The empty Stream.
    Traversable
    An interface for inherently recursive data structures.
    TraversableOnce
    Interface to reduce code duplication of Iterables and Traversables.
    Tree
    A general Tree interface.
    Tree.Order
    Tree traversal order.
